Installing the live_table demo
------------------------------

The web root for the virtual server hosting the demo should contain
the following:

  live_table.html

  js/live_table.js
  js/serf -> serf/js

Other required web assets:

  js/when
  js/require.js
  js/jquery-2.1.1.min.js
  js/w2ui-1.4.3.min.js

  css/w2ui-1.4.3.min.css

Run live_table_server.py in this directory. It will listen for
websocket connections on port 9900 and for serf connections on
port 6506.

Your Apache virtual host config should contain:

	ProxyPass /tables/ ws://localhost:9900/
	ProxyPassReverse /tables/ ws://localhost:9900/

Or for Nginx:

  location /tables/ {
    proxy_pass http://localhost:9900;
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
    proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
    proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
  }

With Nginx you will get disconnects unless you add a heartbeat to the
js code (e.g. setInterval(() => t.count(), 15000);).
